{"title_page": "List of UEFA Champions League top scorers", "text_new": "{{pp-semi-indef}}\n{{short description|Wikimedia list article}}\nThe '''[[UEFA Champions League]]''', known until 1992 as the '''European Champion Clubs' Cup''' or colloquially as the '''European Cup''', is an annual [[association football]] cup competition organised by [[UEFA]] since 1955. Originally a straight knockout competition open only to champion clubs, the tournament was expanded during the 1990s to incorporate a round-robin group phase and more teams. The expansion resulted in more games being played, increasing players' goalscoring chances, thus the list below is weighted in favour of modern players.\n\n==All-time top scorers==\n{{updated|11 March 2020}}<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/newsid=2241732.html|title=Champions League all-time top scorers|date=10 April 2019|publisher=[[UEFA.com]]|accessdate=10 April 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Champions League + European Cup - All-time Topscorers | url=http://www.worldfootball.net/alltime_goalgetter/champions-league/tore/1/ |accessdate=13 February 2018 |website=worldfootball.net}}</ref><ref>Source (unless otherwise indicated): UEFA Champions League Statistics Handbook 2018\u201319. For players active prior to the introduction of the Champions League in 1992, see {{cite web |title=All-time records 1955\u20132018 |publisher=Union of European Football Associations (UEFA) |format=pdf |pages=4\u20138 |url=https://www.uefa.com/MultimediaFiles/Download/EuroExperience/competitions/Publications/02/28/56/90/2285690_DOWNLOAD.pdf |accessdate=3 October 2018 |website=UEFA.com }} For all other players, see: {{cite web |title=Facts and figures |publisher=Union of European Football Associations (UEFA)  |format=pdf |pages=7\u20138 |url=https://www.uefa.com/MultimediaFiles/Download/EuroExperience/competitions/Publications/02/28/56/88/2285688_DOWNLOAD.pdf |accessdate=3 October 2018 |website=UEFA.com}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n| align=\"center\" |\u2021\n| Indicates player from the European Cup era\n|-\n|}\n\nThe table below does not include goals scored in the qualification stage of the competition.<br/>\n'''Bold''' indicates players taking part in the [[2019\u201320 UEFA Champions League]].\n\n<!--\n\nPLEASE DO NOT EDIT UNTIL THE END OF EACH MATCHWEEK TO AVOID ERRORS.\n\nWHEN UPDATING, PLEASE EDIT THE GOALS SCORED, GAMES PLAYED, AND RATIO FOR ALL PLAYERS WHO HAVE PLAYED/SCORED.\n\n-->\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable nowrap\"\n!Rank\n!Player\n!Goals\n!Apps\n!Ratio\n!Years\n!Club(s)\n|-\n|align=center|1\n|{{flagicon|POR}} '''[[Cristiano Ronaldo]]'''\n|align=center|128<!-- NO LIVE UPDATES, UPDATE AFTER EACH MATCHWEEK -->{{refn|group=lower-alpha|Ronaldo additionally scored one goal<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/newsid=2244072.html |title=Lionel Messi and Cristiano Ronaldo goal for goal |website=UEFA.com |accessdate=19 April 2017 |date=18 April 2017 |quote='''Ronaldo''': Debrecen 3-0 (h) 09/08/05, UEFA Champions League third qualifying round |publisher=Union of European Football Associations (UEFA) }}</ref> in four qualification matches.}}\n|align=center|169\n|align=center|{{#expr:128/169 round 2}}\n|align=center|2003\u2013\n|[[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]] (15), [[Real Madrid CF|Real Madrid]] (105), [[Juventus F.C.|Juventus]] (8)\n|-\n|align=center|2\n|{{flagicon|ARG}} '''[[Lionel Messi]]'''\n|align=center|114<!-- NO LIVE UPDATES, UPDATE AFTER EACH MATCHWEEK -->\n|align=center|141\n|align=center|{{#expr:114/140 round 2}}\n|align=center|2005\u2013\n|[[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]]\n|-\n|align=center|3\n|{{flagicon|ESP}} [[Ra\u00fal (footballer)|Ra\u00fal]]\n|align=center|71\n|align=center|142\n|align=center|{{#expr:71/142 round 2}}\n|align=center|1995\u20132011\n|[[Real Madrid CF|Real Madrid]] (66), [[FC Schalke 04|Schalke 04]] (5)\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\" align=center|4\n|{{flagicon|POL}} '''[[Robert Lewandowski]]'''\n|align=center|64\n|al